p: The content of trace elements of CSO was determined by inductively coupled plasma-mass spectrometry (ICP-MS), based on previous methods with minor modifications [ 49]. Briefly, the oven temperature was programmed from 60 °C (3 min hold) to 175 °C at 5 °C/min, maintained at 175 °C for 15 min, then raised to 220 °C at 2 °C/min, and finally held at 220 °C for 10 min.
